cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use resolver in your research or engineering work, please cite it."
title: "resolver: a Go test harness for benchmarking LLMs on agentic tool-use tasks"
abstract: >-
  resolver is a Go test harness that evaluates whether an LLM can serve as the
  resolver for an infrastructure-management agent. Tier 1 runs 31 single-turn
  routing queries across 10 tiers with five gated pass/fail thresholds. Tier 2
  adds multi-turn scenarios with mocked data-producing tools, plus meta-sweeps
  over tool-list size and context size. Scorecards are byte-exact against the
  RESOLVER-VALIDATION-SPEC so cross-model history remains comparable.
type: software
